@{
    Layout = "~/_Layout.cshtml";
    Page.Title = "Bootstrap Formatting";
}

@section banner{
    <div>
        <h3>Exploring Boostrap to format page</h3>
    </div>}

<blockquote>
    Bootstrap is a css stylesheet created as open source. it contains about 10,000 lines of css code.
    Using various aspects of this style sheet can allow us to quickly via classes, block format our web page.
    Bootsrap will also allow for text alignment, setin up nicely formatted grid displays
    create color buttons, banners, etc.<br />
    Alert class allows for color blocking an area plus other stuff. it has built in padding 4 basic messages
    can be obtained by using alert-success, alert-info, alert-warning, and alert-danger
    Default block alignment is left, You can change that using text-xxxx where xxxx is left, right, or center
    <br /><br />
    WARNING: Bootstrap is open source third party and is subject to change. Thus, items that were once available 
    may NOT be available in the future or may be altered. For Bootstrap, 
    if you wish to override a class, it is best to code your own style sheet and NOT alter the NuGet package itself 
</blockquote>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        @* requested the 1st 4 blocks of the row *@
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            left text content
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3 text-md-center text-capitalize text-danger">
        @* requested the next 3 blocks of the row *@
        centered color capuitalized text content
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 text-md-right">
        @* requested the last 5 blocks of the row *@
        <div class="alert alert-danger">
            right text content
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="offset-1">
        <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-primary">primary</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-light">light</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-dark">dark</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-outline-danger">outline danger</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    </div>
</div>




